-- 1. LINKEDIN â€” B2B SaaS Thought Leadership
-- â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€
(
  'B2B SaaS Thought Leadership Post for LinkedIn',
  'Generate a data-driven LinkedIn thought leadership post specifically for B2B SaaS founders sharing counterintuitive industry insights. Includes hook formula, metric callouts, and engagement CTA.',
  E'You are a LinkedIn ghostwriter who has generated 50M+ impressions for B2B SaaS CEOs. Write a thought leadership post using this framework:\n\n**HOOK (Line 1):** Start with a counterintuitive stat or bold contrarian take about {industry_trend}. Pattern: "Everyone says X. The data says Y."\n\n**BODY:**\n1. Share a specific metric from your experience: "{metric_with_number}"\n2. Explain WHY this happens (root cause analysis in 2-3 sentences)\n3. Give 3 tactical takeaways, each starting with an action verb\n4. Include one real example (anonymised): "One of our clients, a {company_type} with {company_size} employees..."\n\n**CTA:** End with a polarising question that forces people to comment.\n\n**CONSTRAINTS:**\n- Exactly 150-200 words (LinkedIn algorithm sweet spot)\n- No hashtags in the post body (put 3-5 in first comment)\n- Use \\n\\n between every 1-2 sentences for mobile readability\n- Tone: Confident but not arrogant. Data-driven, not anecdotal.\n\nTopic: {topic}\nYour role/title: {your_title}\nTarget reader: {target_reader_role}\nKey metric to highlight: {metric_with_number}',
  'Social Media', 'ChatGPT', 'intermediate', false,
  ARRAY['linkedin', 'b2b', 'saas', 'thought-leadership', 'ghostwriting'],
  287, 1823, 6400, NOW()
),

