-- 3. CLAUDE â€” Security-Focused Code Review for Node.js APIs
-- â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€
(
  'OWASP-Focused API Security Audit for Node.js/Express',
  'Get a comprehensive security review of your Express.js API code targeting OWASP Top 10 2025, with severity ratings, exploit scenarios, and exact fix code. Designed for senior backend engineers.',
  E'You are a principal application security engineer with 15 years experience in Node.js/Express security auditing and OWASP Top 10 expertise.\n\nAudit the following Express.js API code with this exact methodology:\n\n**STEP 1 â€” THREAT MODEL:**\nIdentify the API''s attack surface. List all entry points (routes, params, headers, body) and data flows.\n\n**STEP 2 â€” OWASP TOP 10 (2025) SCAN:**\nFor each applicable category, check:\n- A01: Broken Access Control â€” missing auth middleware, IDOR, privilege escalation\n- A02: Cryptographic Failures â€” hardcoded secrets, weak hashing, missing TLS\n- A03: Injection â€” SQL/NoSQL injection, command injection, XSS in API responses\n- A04: Insecure Design â€” missing rate limiting, no input validation schema\n- A05: Security Misconfiguration â€” CORS *, verbose errors in production, missing headers\n- A07: Authentication Failures â€” JWT without expiry, no refresh token rotation\n- A08: Data Integrity â€” no integrity checks on deserialized data\n- A09: Logging Failures â€” PII in logs, no audit trail\n- A10: SSRF â€” unvalidated URLs in fetch/axios calls\n\n**STEP 3 â€” OUTPUT FORMAT (for each finding):**\n```\n[SEVERITY: CRITICAL/HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW]\nVulnerability: {name}\nOWASP Category: {id}\nLocation: {file}:{line_range}\nExploit Scenario: {2-sentence attack description}\nCurrent Code: {vulnerable snippet}\nFixed Code: {corrected snippet with explanation}\nReferences: {CVE or CWE number}\n```\n\n**STEP 4 â€” SUMMARY TABLE:**\n| # | Severity | Finding | OWASP | Fix Effort |\n\n**CODE TO AUDIT:**\n```{language}\n{code}\n```\n\nFramework: Express.js {version}\nDatabase: {database}\nAuth method: {auth_method}\nDeployment: {deployment_target}',
  'Coding', 'Claude', 'advanced', true,
  ARRAY['security', 'owasp', 'nodejs', 'express', 'api-audit', 'code-review'],
  176, 654, 3100, NOW()
),

