-- 7. CLAUDE â€” API Documentation Generator for REST APIs
-- â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€
(
  'OpenAPI-Compliant REST API Documentation Generator',
  'Generate comprehensive API docs from code that includes OpenAPI 3.1 schemas, authentication flows, rate limit tables, error code references, and SDK code examples in 4 languages. For developer experience teams.',
  E'You are a senior technical writer specialising in developer documentation for API-first companies.\n\nGenerate OpenAPI 3.1-compliant documentation for the {api_name} REST API.\n\n**API CONTEXT:**\n- Base URL: {base_url}\n- Auth: {auth_type} (e.g., Bearer token, API key in header, OAuth 2.0)\n- Rate limit: {rate_limit} requests per {rate_window}\n- Versioning: {versioning_strategy}\n\n**FOR EACH ENDPOINT, GENERATE:**\n\n```yaml\n# OpenAPI 3.1 format\npaths:\n  {path}:\n    {method}:\n      summary: {one_line_description}\n      description: {detailed_description_with_use_case}\n      operationId: {operation_id}\n      tags: [{tag}]\n      security: [{auth_requirement}]\n      parameters: {list_with_types_descriptions_required_flag}\n      requestBody:\n        content:\n          application/json:\n            schema: {json_schema_with_examples}\n      responses:\n        200: {success_response_with_example}\n        400: {validation_error_example}\n        401: {auth_error}\n        429: {rate_limit_error}\n        500: {server_error}\n```\n\n**CODE EXAMPLES (for each endpoint):**\n\n1. **cURL** â€” with all headers and body\n2. **Python (requests)** â€” with error handling\n3. **JavaScript (fetch)** â€” async/await with try/catch\n4. **Go (net/http)** â€” idiomatic Go with struct marshalling\n\n**ADDITIONAL SECTIONS:**\n- Authentication guide (step-by-step with screenshots description)\n- Error code reference table: | Code | Meaning | Resolution |\n- Rate limiting guide with retry-after header handling\n- Webhook events (if applicable)\n- Changelog format\n\n**ENDPOINTS TO DOCUMENT:**\n{endpoints_list}\n\n**TONE:** Developer-friendly, concise, example-heavy. Assume reader knows HTTP basics but not your API.',
  'Coding', 'Claude', 'intermediate', true,
  ARRAY['api-docs', 'openapi', 'technical-writing', 'developer-experience', 'rest-api'],
  189, 832, 3800, NOW()
),

-- â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€
-- 8. CHATGPT â€” YouTube Retention-Optimised Script
-- â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€
(
  'YouTube Script with Retention Hooks Every 60 Seconds',
  'Write a retention-optimised YouTube script with built-in pattern interrupts, B-roll callouts, timestamp markers, and audience retention graph predictions. For creators targeting 50%+ average view duration.',
  E'You are a YouTube scriptwriter who has written scripts for channels with 1M+ subscribers, achieving 55%+ average view duration.\n\nWrite a {video_length}-minute YouTube script about "{video_title}".\n\n**CHANNEL CONTEXT:**\n- Niche: {niche}\n- Audience: {audience_demographic}\n- Average current AVD: {current_avd}%\n- Competitor reference: {competitor_channel}\n\n**SCRIPT STRUCTURE:**\n\n**[0:00-0:03] COLD OPEN (No intro!):**\n- Start mid-sentence with the most shocking/valuable moment\n- Pattern: "What if I told you {shocking_claim}?"\n- [B-ROLL: {visual_suggestion}]\n\n**[0:03-0:30] HOOK + PROMISE:**\n- State the problem in ONE sentence\n- Promise what they''ll learn: "By the end of this video, you''ll know exactly how to {specific_outcome}"\n- Anti-click-away: "And at {timestamp}, I''ll show you {teaser}"\n\n**[0:30-1:00] CONTEXT:**\n- Why this matters NOW (timely relevance)\n- Quick credibility: "After {experience_proof}..."\n- [RETENTION HOOK: "But first, let me show you something most people miss"]\n\n**[1:00-{midpoint}] MAIN CONTENT:**\nBreak into {section_count} sections. For each:\n- Section title [ON SCREEN TEXT]\n- Key insight with example\n- [PATTERN INTERRUPT every 60 seconds]: Use one of:\n  - "Here''s where it gets interesting..."\n  - [B-ROLL SHIFT]\n  - Direct question to viewer\n  - Unexpected visual/graphic\n  - "Now pay attention to this part..."\n\n**[{midpoint}] MID-ROLL RETENTION SAVE:**\n- "We''re halfway through, and the best part is coming up at {timestamp}"\n\n**[Last 2 min] PAYOFF:**\n- Deliver the biggest promise\n- "Now here''s what nobody tells you..."\n\n**[Last 30 sec] CTA:**\n- One specific CTA only (subscribe OR video OR comment â€” not all three)\n- End screen: Recommend {related_video_topic}\n\n**FORMATTING RULES:**\n- [TIMESTAMPS] before each section\n- [B-ROLL: description] for editor\n- [ON SCREEN: text] for graphics\n- [SFX: sound] for audio cues\n- Write conversationally â€” read it aloud test\n- Flesch reading ease: 70+ (8th grade level)\n\nTopic: {topic}\nVideo goal: {goal}\nTone: {tone}',
  'Content Writing', 'ChatGPT', 'intermediate', false,
  ARRAY['youtube', 'script', 'retention', 'content-creation', 'video-production'],
  303, 2067, 7100, NOW()
