(
  'Seed-Stage Startup Brand Identity & Positioning Framework',
  'Develop a complete brand identity system for seed-stage startups including positioning matrix, voice guidelines, naming conventions, and launch messaging. Built for founders who need investor-ready brand docs.',
  E'You are a brand strategist from a top agency (Pentagram/Wolff Olins level) working with a seed-stage startup.\n\nDevelop a complete brand identity framework for {company_name}.\n\n**COMPANY BRIEF:**\n- Product: {product_description}\n- Industry: {industry}\n- Stage: Seed / Pre-Series A\n- Funding: {funding_amount}\n- Founders: {founder_backgrounds}\n- Current customers: {customer_count}\n\n**DELIVERABLES:**\n\n**1. POSITIONING MATRIX:**\n| Dimension | Our Position | Competitor A | Competitor B |\n|-----------|-------------|-------------|-------------|\n| Price     |             |             |             |\n| Speed     |             |             |             |\n| Quality   |             |             |             |\n| Target    |             |             |             |\n\n**2. BRAND POSITIONING STATEMENT (Madison & Vine format):**\n"For [target audience] who [need/pain point], {company_name} is the [category] that [key benefit] because [reason to believe]."\n\n**3. MISSION / VISION / VALUES:**\n- Mission: [action-oriented, present tense, max 15 words]\n- Vision: [aspirational, future state, max 20 words]\n- Values: [5 values with 1-sentence explanation each]\n\n**4. BRAND PERSONALITY (Aaker model):**\nRate 1-5 on: Sincerity, Excitement, Competence, Sophistication, Ruggedness\nWith justification for each.\n\n**5. VOICE & TONE GUIDELINES:**\n| Context | Tone | Example Do | Example Don''t |\n|---------|------|-----------|---------------|\n| Website | | | |\n| Email | | | |\n| Social | | | |\n| Support | | | |\n| Investor pitch | | | |\n\n**6. MESSAGING HIERARCHY:**\n- Tagline (max 6 words)\n- Elevator pitch (30 seconds / 75 words)\n- Boilerplate (press release style, 100 words)\n- Investor one-liner\n\n**7. VISUAL DIRECTION:**\n- Primary color + meaning\n- Secondary palette (3 colors)\n- Typography direction (serif vs sans, modern vs classic)\n- Photography/illustration style\n- Logo direction (wordmark vs symbol vs combo)\n\n**8. NAMING CONVENTIONS:**\n- Product naming pattern\n- Feature naming pattern\n- Content naming pattern\n\nCompetitors to differentiate from: {competitors}',
  'Business', 'ChatGPT', 'advanced', true,
  ARRAY['brand-strategy', 'startup', 'positioning', 'seed-stage', 'identity-design'],
  156, 678, 2300, NOW()
),

