-- 15. CLAUDE â€” Research Paper Analysis & Summary
-- â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€
(
  'Academic Research Paper Deep Analysis with Methodology Critique',
  'Break down a research paper with structured analysis of methodology, statistical validity, bias assessment, and practical implications. For PhD students, researchers, and science communicators.',
  E'You are a peer reviewer for Nature/Science-tier journals with expertise in {field_of_study}.\n\nAnalyse the following research paper with academic rigour:\n\n**PAPER DETAILS:**\n- Title: "{paper_title}"\n- Authors: {authors}\n- Journal/Source: {journal}\n- Year: {year}\n- DOI: {doi}\n\n**ANALYSIS FRAMEWORK:**\n\n**1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY (1 paragraph, 100 words):**\nWhat did they study, how, and what did they find? Written for an educated non-specialist.\n\n**2. RESEARCH QUESTION & HYPOTHESIS:**\n- Primary research question\n- Hypothesis (explicit or implicit)\n- How this fills a gap in existing literature\n\n**3. METHODOLOGY CRITIQUE:**\n| Aspect | Assessment | Concern Level |\n|--------|-----------|---------------|\n| Sample size | {adequate/small/large} | {low/medium/high} |\n| Sampling method | {random/convenience/stratified} | |\n| Control group | {present/absent/inadequate} | |\n| Blinding | {single/double/none} | |\n| Duration | {sufficient/insufficient} | |\n| Reproducibility | {described/vague/missing} | |\n\n**4. STATISTICAL ANALYSIS:**\n- Methods used: {list_statistical_methods}\n- p-values: Are they meaningful or p-hacked?\n- Effect sizes: Reported? Practically significant?\n- Confidence intervals: Reported?\n- Multiple comparisons correction: Applied?\n\n**5. BIAS ASSESSMENT (Cochrane-style):**\n- Selection bias: {low/unclear/high}\n- Performance bias: {low/unclear/high}\n- Detection bias: {low/unclear/high}\n- Attrition bias: {low/unclear/high}\n- Reporting bias: {low/unclear/high}\n- Funding bias: Check funding sources\n\n**6. KEY FINDINGS (numbered, specific):**\n- Finding 1: {with exact numbers/stats}\n- Finding 2: ...\n- Surprising finding: ...\n\n**7. LIMITATIONS (author-stated + your additions):**\n- Authors acknowledge: {list}\n- Additional limitations I identify: {list}\n\n**8. PRACTICAL IMPLICATIONS:**\n- For practitioners in {field}: {implications}\n- For future research: {suggestions}\n- For public understanding: {key_takeaway}\n\n**9. RELATED WORK:**\n- 3 papers that support these findings\n- 2 papers that contradict these findings\n\n**10. OVERALL ASSESSMENT:**\n- Quality score: {1-10}/10\n- Novelty: {low/medium/high}\n- Impact: {low/medium/high}\n- Recommendation: {accept/minor revision/major revision/reject}\n\n{paper_content_or_abstract}',
  'Learning', 'Claude', 'advanced', false,
  ARRAY['research', 'academic', 'peer-review', 'methodology', 'science', 'phd'],
