-- â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€
(
  'TED-Style Talk Script with Story Arc & Audience Engagement Cues',
  'Write a TED-format talk script with precise timing, story arc, stage direction, slide cues, and emotional beat mapping. For speakers preparing for conferences, TEDx, or company all-hands.',
  E'You are a TED talk coach who has prepared 40+ speakers for TEDx stages, including 5 talks with 1M+ views.\n\nWrite a {duration}-minute TED-style talk about "{talk_title}".\n\n**SPEAKER PROFILE:**\n- Name: {speaker_name}\n- Expertise: {expertise}\n- Speaking style: {style}\n- Personal story to incorporate: {personal_story}\n\n**AUDIENCE:**\n- Who: {audience_description}\n- Size: {audience_size}\n- What they believe now: {current_belief}\n- What you want them to believe after: {desired_belief}\n\n**TALK STRUCTURE (Kurt Vonnegut Story Arc):**\n\n**[0:00] OPENING â€” "The Moment" (60 seconds):**\n- Start with a SPECIFIC moment in time: "On {date}, at {time}, I was standing in {place}..."\n- No "Good morning" or "I''m here to talk about"\n- Create vivid sensory detail\n- [STAGE DIRECTION: Walk to center stage, no slides]\n\n**[1:00] THE PROBLEM â€” "The World Before" (3 minutes):**\n- Paint the problem with a concrete example\n- Use data: "{stat}" â€” [SLIDE: {slide_description}]\n- Make it personal: How does this affect THEM (the audience)?\n- Build tension: "And it''s getting worse because..."\n- [EMOTIONAL BEAT: Concern â†’ Frustration]\n\n**[4:00] THE TURN â€” "But Then..." (2 minutes):**\n- The moment of discovery/insight\n- "That''s when I realized {insight}"\n- Counter-intuitive twist that challenges the status quo\n- [STAGE DIRECTION: Pause 3 seconds. Let it land.]\n- [EMOTIONAL BEAT: Surprise â†’ Curiosity]\n\n**[6:00] THE SOLUTION â€” "The Idea Worth Spreading" (4 minutes):**\n- State the core idea in ONE sentence (your TED idea)\n- Support with 3 pillars:\n  - Pillar 1: {evidence_type} â€” [SLIDE: {visual}]\n  - Pillar 2: {example/case_study}\n  - Pillar 3: {scientific_backing}\n- Make it actionable: "Here''s what this means for you..."\n- [EMOTIONAL BEAT: Hope â†’ Excitement]\n\n**[10:00] THE STORY â€” "Proof It Works" (3 minutes):**\n- Tell ONE powerful story of transformation\n- Character: {character}\n- Before state â†’ Struggle â†’ After state\n- Include dialogue: "She looked at me and said..."\n- [STAGE DIRECTION: Move to the left side of stage]\n- [EMOTIONAL BEAT: Empathy â†’ Inspiration]\n\n**[13:00] THE CLOSE â€” "Your Turn" ({remaining_time} minutes):**\n- Circle back to the opening story\n- Challenge the audience: "Tomorrow morning, I want you to {specific_action}"\n- End with the strongest sentence of the talk\n- [STAGE DIRECTION: Return to center. Pause. Eye contact. Walk off.]\n- DO NOT say "Thank you" â€” let the audience start the applause\n\n**SPEAKER NOTES:**\n- Pace: {words_per_minute} WPM (aim for 140-160)\n- Pauses: Mark with [PAUSE] â€” minimum 5 strategic pauses\n- Emphasis words: **bold** for vocal stress\n- Humor points: {joke_opportunities}\n- Audience interaction: {interaction_moment}',
  'Content Writing', 'ChatGPT', 'advanced', false,
  ARRAY['ted-talk', 'public-speaking', 'conference', 'storytelling', 'presentation'],
  267, 934, 3800, NOW()
),

